{
  "text": "The other members of the SGLT family seem to fulfill functions other than glucose transport. SGLT3 (SLC5A4) is a putative glucose sensor in different tissues [CITATION_1] . SGLT4 (SLC5A9) and SGLT5 (SLC5A10) exhibit high affinity towards mannose, thus they can function as mannose transporters [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . SGLT6 (SLC5A11) alias SMIT2 (sodium-myoinositol-cotransporter 2) mediates inositol transport [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
